{[%evp 0,25,24,22,22,4,32,16,64,64,64,41,55,50,63,57,59,59,51,44,92,77,98,32,
81,89,73,73]} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. h4 c5 (5... Nf6 {
An artificial way of preventing h4-h5. Black wastes a valuable tempo and
retreats his knight from the centre.} 6. e4 Bg7 7. e5 {I find this as the most
energetic, although 7.d4 has scored also very well.} Ng4 (7... Nd5 8. h5 Nc6 9.
d4 $16 {, followed by 10.h6 is too passive for Black.}) 8. d4 O-O ({The
immediate} 8... c5 $6 {runs into} 9. Bb5+ $1 Bd7 10. e6 $1 fxe6 11. Ng5 {
, and Black is busted.}) 9. h5 c5 {The only attempt to make any counter-play.}
10. hxg6 hxg6 11. d5 $1 {White sacrifices a pawn to maintain the initiative.} Nxe5
{This position occurred in Valenzuela Gomez, F - Cruz, J Barcelona 2019} ({
In the event of} 11... Nd7 12. e6 fxe6 13. Qc2 Nde5 14. Nxe5 Nxe5 15. f4 exd5
16. fxe5 $16 {Black doesn't have sufficient compensation for a piece as his
king is very exposed.}) {White should have continued} 12. Nxe5 $146 Bxe5 13.
Qd2 $1 Bg7 14. Qf4 $40 {Black can hardly withstand such a strong attack.}) (
5... h6 6. e4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 Bg7 8. d4 {is covered with 5...Nxc3}) ({The same
about} 5... h5 6. e4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 Bg7 {- 5...Nxc3.}) (5... Bg4 $6 {is
premature. White can claim its drawbacks with} 6. Qb3 $1 Nb6 7. Ng5 $1 e6 8. f3
{The bishop is trapped!} h6 9. Nxf7 Kxf7 10. fxg4 $16 {Black's king-side was
ruined in Pogorelov, R - Cortes Artigas, J Coria del Rio 2002}) (5... Nc6 {
is quite a common move, but after} 6. h5 Bg7 {it transposes to 5...Bg7.}) 6. h5
Bg7 {This position often arises with 5...Bg7 6.h5 c5.} ({In case of} 6... Nxc3
{White can play 7.bxc3, transposing to 5... Nxc3, but there is also another
attractive option:} 7. dxc3 Qxd1+ 8. Kxd1 Bg7 9. e4 {White takes the upper
hand in the centre and threatens to trap the bishop with 10.h5 Bf6 11.e5.} Bg4
10. h6 Bf6 11. Kc2 Nc6 12. Be3 b6 {This was Deac, B - Atanasov, A Chess.com INT
2022 Here I mostly like} 13. Bb5 $146 Rc8 14. Rad1 O-O 15. Bf4 $16 {Black is
very cramped on both sides of the board.}) 7. h6 Bf6 8. e4 {A well-timed move.
Black is forced to capture on c3 to avoid the loss of a piece.} Nxc3 {We have
been following the game Gunina, V - Lagno, K Chess.com INT 2020} 9. dxc3 $5 $146
Qc7 (9... Qxd1+ {leads to the same kind of unpleasant endgame as 6...Nxc3:} 10.
Kxd1 Nc6 11. Bb5 Bd7 12. Be3 b6 13. a4 Ne5 14. Ke2 $14 {Black struggles to
connect his rooks without making big concessions.}) 10. Be3 O-O 11. Nd2 $1 {
preparing the way for f2-f4.} Nd7 12. f4 e5 13. f5 $36 {Black's king-side is
under strong pressure in view of the subsequent g2-g4-g5.} *

